commit.message: Prevent installation of older pre-split pyct alongside pyct-core.
Added missing upload of pyct-core.

Add pyct.build (#45)

* Moved pyctbuild into pyct.build. pyct can therefore become the standard build time dependency of pyviz projects that need to package examples. pyct.build itself has no dependencies. pip install pyct or conda install pyct-core will be ways to get pyct.build. To get the user commands (which have dependencies), it will be pip install pyct[cmd] or conda install pyct (following the pattern of minimal dependencies for pip packages with optional extras, vs multiple conda packages with the default being all typical dependencies).

* Use setup.cfg for packaging metadata. Even if in future some other file becomes standard (e.g. pyproject.toml), at least moving to some kind of config file and away from running code is a step in the right direction.
